results.name: Smallest member of A002473 whose digital product = A002473(n), or 0 if no such number exists.
comment: Next term (A002473(n) = 21) is either 0 or > 10^100. - _David Wasserman_, Jan 27 2005
a(17) = 0, because A002473(17) = 21 = 3*7 and the last two digits of every member of A002473 greater than 7 contain a digit other than 1, 3, and 7. - _Robert Israel_, Nov 23 2019
Similarly, a(n) = 0 whenever n >=17 and A002473(n) is coprime to 10. - _Robert Israel_, Nov 24 2019
example: 20 is a member of A002473 and the corresponding term is 45 which is also a member of A002473.
